Good morning,

In yesterday=E2=80=99s Article I included a chart of Amazon=E2=80=99s North=
 American Retail sales on a 3-year over 3-year basis. However, given that A=
mazon=E2=80=99s sales mix continues to shift towards 3rd-party merchants (f=
rom whom Amazon only recognizes fees), this is an inaccurate measurement; a=
